author: WSFA 12 News Staff
title: Hardees Fever Star Athlete of the Week 2015
text:
Hardees Fever Star Athlete of the Week 2015 By WSFA 12 News Staff Follow @wsfa12news MONTGOMERY, AL (WSFA) - 
It's week eight of the Hardee's Fever Star Athlete competition, and three more football players have been selected as finalists based on their performances Friday night. Now it's your turn to vote for your favorite. ( Mobile users, click here to vote ) 
Vote each week and we'll announce the winner during our 6 sportscast on Thursday! 
This week's finalists were: Running back Teddy Brooks of Tallassee rushed 138 yards and had four touchdowns as the Tigers beat Marbury. Quarterback Nathan Rourke, the "Canadian Cannon" of Edgewood, passed for 260 yards and had four touchdowns with only three incompletions in the Cats' win over Northside. Running back Deshon Cowlin of Pike County rushed for 171 yards and had three touchdowns over Wicksburg. 
Our weekly winners and candidates for athlete of the year: 
WEEK 01 - Barton Lester - Montgomery Academy 
WEEK 02 - Dawson Roy - Prattville Christian Academy 
WEEK 03 - Jamal Hourel - Andalusia 
WEEK 04 - Blake Underwood - St. James 
WEEK 05 - Jacquez Payton - Georgiana 
WEEK 06 - Tommy Spivey - Brantley High School 
WEEK 07 - Robert Adams - Trinity Presbyterian 
WEEK 08 - Deshon Cowlin - Pike County 
WEEK 09 - n/a
